TITLE: Initializing Adjust SDK with First Session Delay in Android
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to initialize the Adjust SDK with a delayed first session. The SDK can be started in delayed mode by calling 'enableFirstSessionDelay' on the AdjustConfig instance, and the delay can be ended by calling 'endFirstSessionDelay' on the Adjust instance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/adjust/android_sdk/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
AdjustConfig config = new AdjustConfig(this, APP_TOKEN, ENVIRONMENT);
config.enableFirstSessionDelay();
Adjust.onCreate(config);

// Later, when ready to start tracking
Adjust.endFirstSessionDelay();
```

